; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your controller before
; running on a machine. Output is not guaranteed safe for any real machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Before production: (1) air cut / dry run — spindle off, Z high, reduced feed
; (2) single-axis jog tests if you changed WCS or macros (3) shallow first cut
; in soft stock (4) compare a short program to a known-good file for this control
; See docs/MACHINES.md — safe Z, WCS, units (G20/G21), spindle M-codes, arc support.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Spindle/coolant: profile dialect inserts snippets below — Grbl, Mach3, and others
; differ on M3/M4/M5, S-word RPM, and coolant (M7/M8/M9). Confirm on your control.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Tool change: this template does not emit M6, ATC macros, or tool-length comp.
; It assumes a single-tool program unless you add tool-change blocks yourself.
; Verify the full sequence (spindle stop, safe Z, M6/T/H if used) on your control
; before running multi-tool jobs.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): 300 x 200 x 100
G21        ; G21=mm / G20=inch — must match controller defaults at power-on
G90              ; absolute distance mode
G17              ; XY plane (typical for G2/G3 arcs)
; Operation: RPM Clamped Min
; Spindle on (dialect from machine profile — change profile if M3/S/RPM differ)
M3 S6000
G0 X0 Y0 Z10
G0 X5 Y5 Z5
G1 Z-1.000 F300
G1 X15 Y5 F800
G1 X15 Y15 F800
G1 X5 Y15 F800
G1 X5 Y5 F800
G0 Z10
; Spindle off (dialect snippet — usually M5)
M5
; Retract Z to safe clearance and park (adjust to your machine's preferred home)
G0 Z100 ; safe Z retract — adjust to your actual safe clearance
